      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-primary-800 animate-on-scroll">
        About the Workshop
      </h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6 animate-on-scroll">
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          As generative and agentic AI systems become deeply integrated into EDA automation, chip design workflows, and semiconductor development pipelines, ensuring their security, privacy, and verifiability has become mission-critical. These systems increasingly generate RTL, verify designs, interact with sensitive intellectual property, and reason autonomously across complex toolchains — creating unprecedented attack surfaces and trust challenges.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          SPGAI provides the first cross-layer forum at DAC dedicated to the secure and private deployment of generative and agentic AI systems. By unifying advances in cryptography, hardware architecture, verifiable computing, AI security, and design automation, the workshop brings together leading researchers and industry practitioners to establish a roadmap for building trustworthy AI systems that interact safely with hardware, tools, and sensitive design assets.
        </p>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The workshop will feature a rich mix of keynotes, paper sessions, and interactive discussions. By uniting researchers, engineers, and innovators from academia and industry, SPGAI aims to push the frontier of secure and private system design for generative and agentic AI — setting new standards for trustworthy AI deployment in hardware and EDA workflows.
        </p>
      
      </div>
